#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
archguard – aggressive security auditing & hardening for Arch Linux

This tool goes beyond basic hardening: it runs deep security scans,
checks for rootkits, vulnerabilities, misconfigurations, and integrity issues.
It can also apply aggressive hardening modules (kernel params, service sandboxing,
USB lockdown, etc.) with full reversibility.

THREAT MODEL: This is designed for a personal workstation that requires
high assurance. It assumes the user is willing
to review findings and accept potential breakage. It is NOT for production
servers without careful testing. It will install additional packages
(rkhunter, lynis, aide, clamav, etc.) if you allow it.

The tool is modular: each module performs a specific task (audit or hardening).
All changes are backed up and can be reverted. Audit modules are read-only
and only report findings.

If you dislike colors/emoji, use --quiet or --no-color.
"""

